at high currents, the peak efficiency will be inbetween (see eta_max above).

Auslastung / Generator capacity usage. Red is only tolerable to a certain degree. At some point the mechanic will break, even if the rotor is electrically/mechanically deccelerated to not go over the rated RPM.
Assumes the generator is prevented to generate more than its design power. (see red alert background in the power / power_nominal ratio above)
ONLY CONSTRUCT A WIND POWER PLANT IF YOU HAVE HIGH WINDS! IT'S NOT A MIRACLE MACHINE. NO WIND => NO POWER OUTPUT!
ONLY CONSTRUCT A HYDRO POWER PLANT IF YOU HAVE EITHER HIGH HEIGHT DIFFERENCE (head) OR HIGH FLOW (water masses)! KEEP WAY FOR FISH IN BOTH DIRECTIONS (up- and downstream).

OFTEN A SIMPLE CROSS-FLOW TURBINE PRODUCES MORE AVERAGE OUTPUT IF VARIABLES LIKE FLOW RATE VARY A LOT OVER YEAR,WATER FLOW RATE AS ITS EFFICIENCY REMAINS STABLE OVER A WIDE RANGE (contrary to some others, e.g. pelton is sensible to too much water while turgo turbine isn't so much). ESPECIALLY IF NEITHER AVAILABLE HEAD NOR FLOW RATE ARE CONVINCING/HIGH ENOUGH.

IT'S GOOD TO GET AN IDEA OF HOW MUCH ENERGY YOU CAN GET AND TO TEST ELECTRONICS PRINCIPLES. LATER YOU CAN STILL CONSTRUCT THE PENSTOCK WITH THE 30m HEAD PELTON OR DIRECT DRIVE TURGO TURBINE. OR THE HIGH WATER MASSES FRANCIS TURBINE OR KAPLAN TURBINE. OR VORTEX OR WHATEVER OTHER TURBINE YOU WANT TO TEST. DON'T EXCEPT MIRACLES THOUGH AND KEEP US INFORMED ABOUT RESULTS OF EXPERIMENTS AS WE DO TOO!

Assumes the poles are placed at 2/3 * radius.
the higher the greater the 'reduction' => more torque

Note the pole height as high as possible because mostly the radial components contribute to the torque. compromise: e.g. oval. Though if thinking of a generator then better circular to ease current induction?, see Lebowski's explanation endlesssphere.
OR: (Attention, pole spacing not considered!! As it required iterating to solve.)
Only multiples of phase count! e.g. x * 3 if 3 phases!
NOTE: The rotor magnets must be contained within the outer bounds of the stator windings to fully utilize the magnetic flux!
